The paper focuses on the communication aspects of ultra-narrowband IoT networks, which are typically studied in the computer science subfield of networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also involves the analysis of transmission success probability and network connection density, which are topics commonly studied in information theory (cs.IT) and control systems (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of multiple bands and the impact of interference, which are relevant to multimedia systems (cs.MM) and cryptography and security (cs.CR).
